    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-23T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-23T14:00:00-05:00" n="211"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 676</seg>
                </opener>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">249.1111–<persName corresp="#p_OW1">Oatis,
                        William</persName>/5–2351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Czechoslovakia (<persName corresp="#p_BEO1"
                            type="from">Briggs</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Praha</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-23T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 23, 1951—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>744. <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> today sent note to <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> replying communication quoted <gloss
                        target="#t_EMBTEL1">Embtel</gloss> 732, May 21:<note n="1" xml:id="d211fn1"
                        >The substance of telegram 732 is contained in the second paragraph of the
                        Embassy note quoted in the telegram printed here. (249.1111–<persName
                            corresp="#p_OW1">Oatis, William</persName>/5–2151)</note>
                </p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“<gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> US presents compliments etc. and refers
                        Min’s note May 21, which stated that Amer radio broadcasts had transmitted
                        malevolent and untruthful interpretation of conversation on May 16, between
                            <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> and Amer Amb concerning Mr.
                            <persName corresp="#p_OW1">Oatis</persName>,<note n="2" xml:id="d211fn2"
                            >See telegram 721, Document 674.</note> and that therefore Min saw no
                        reason for case of <persName corresp="#p_OW1">Oatis</persName> to be subj
                        any further discussion.</p>
                    <p>“<gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> is astonished at importance attached by
                        Min to public speculation concerning conversation between <gloss
                            target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> and Amb. <gloss target="#t_Emb1"
                            >Emb</gloss>’s report to Dept of State describing conversation was
                        accurate report and did not contain any statement to effect Czech Govt wld
                        release <persName corresp="#p_OW1">Oatis</persName> if broadcasts of <gloss
                            target="#t_RFE1">RFE</gloss> were stopped. Dept on its own initiative
                        informed press on May 21, ’51, it had no knowledge any Czech proposal this
                        nature. More explicit denial might have been difficult for reason that
                            <gloss target="#t_RFE1">RFE</gloss> had in fact been mentioned by <gloss
                            target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>. <gloss target="#t_RFE1">RFE</gloss>
                        was mentioned on two occasions by <persName corresp="#p_SV1"
                            >Siroky</persName> during Amb’s conversation on May 16, seeking release
                        of <persName corresp="#p_OW1">Oatis</persName>, as creating unfavorable
                        atmosphere. Amb so reported to his Govt.</p>
                    <p>“With respect to origin report to which Min’s note takes exception, <gloss
                            target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>’s info is that report came in first
                        instance from Vienna, not Wash.</p>
                    <p>“<gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> accordingly requests that <gloss
                            target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> kindly renew discussions in case of
                            <persName corresp="#p_OW1">Oatis</persName> with Amb, in accordance with
                        Min’s offer made during aforesaid conversation on May 16.</p>
                    <p>“<gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> avails etc.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SV1">Siroky</persName> again in Slovakia to return May 28.
                    In meantime we are sending separate note stating if notwithstanding continuing
                        <pb facs="0396" n="1362" xml:id="pg_1362"/> representations Czecho Govt
                    insists <persName corresp="#p_OW1">Oatis</persName> trial, then advance
                    notification requested and arrangements by <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> for presence <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> officials
                    and interpreter (VC <persName corresp="#p_JJA1">Johnson</persName> and
                        <persName>Mary Horak</persName>).</p>
                <p>Greatly appreciates <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 598 and 602<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d211fn3">Dated May 21 and 22, respectively; they reported that
                        the Department of State had not been able to ascertain the origin of reports
                        concerning a possible “<persName corresp="#p_OW1">Oatis</persName> for
                            <gloss target="#t_RFE1">RFE</gloss>” exchange and that the Department
                        itself had not been the source. (249.1111–<persName corresp="#p_OW1">Oatis,
                            William</persName>/5–2051 and 5–2251)</note> re efforts ascertain origin
                        “<gloss target="#t_RFE1">RFE</gloss> for <persName corresp="#p_OW1"
                        >Oatis</persName>” story.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BEO1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Briggs</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
